headline: December Retail Sales Fell Short. Worries About the Economy Curbed Holiday Spending.
summary: Consumer spending was flat in December, indicating shoppers were more hesitant to buy than economists expected.  Retail sales were virtually unchanged in December from November, according to data released Tuesday by the Census Bureau.  “The holiday shopping season was solid, but not spectacular,” said Heather Long, chief economist at Navy Federal Credit Union.
